<hl>
<seg id=1> Russian Prime Minister talked about Russian economic situation. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, (Moscow), (8 January) Russian Prime Minister Vladimirputin said on a government conference that the major achievement in 1997 was creating the main conditions for economic development in Russia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to the report from Russian national agency-Tas Agency, Vladimirputin said that last year in Russia the total output value increased by 1.2% over 1996. The industrial output value had 3.2% increase, and the total retail value increased by 3.9%. The annual inflation rate was 11%, which was half of that in 1996. Personal income had 2.5%increase. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> At the same time Vladimirputin pointed out that there were a few problems last year, e.g. tax revenue was not high; investment plan didn't meet the target; favorable balance of foreign trade reduced; the government financial and monetary measures were not effective enough. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Talking about this year, Vladimirputin said that they were drafting a plan for structure reform and economic development, and they planned to submit the draft to the enlarged congress on 26 February for discussion. </seg>
<seg id=6> According to this plan, the total output value in Russia next year would increase by 2%, and the inflation rate would reduce by 5% to 8%. </seg>
</p>
